<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-09T23:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-09T23:30:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/1783: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">William Phillips</persName>,
                                Personal Representative of President Roosevelt in India, to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-10T11:00:00+06:30">February
                                    10, 1943—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 10—3:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>120. The Viceroy has just informed me that Gandhi started his fast this
                            morning (my 118, February 9, 11 p.m.)</p>
                        <p>Under the circumstances I am postponing any further tours for the time
                            being.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>